settings.description: The improved version of my other castle: ''Bowser's Revenge'', I hope you like it!
Use the POW block to clear rows of enemies while solving puzzles in this watery ghost house.
Embarking a Journey on the First Unused level but It's Improved by a little bit, Good luck finding the hidden Ace coins!
Re-issuing old levels, so I don't have to make levels! Lazy, ain't it? (Though this will only happen to levels that are old and I have no plans on doing anything with)
Fun Fact: I'm terrible at making underwater levels, so I just decided to take out the water in the underwater, thus creating an... under level.
strange spinning spheres with arrows on them! hop on top of such, and go for a ride! think you can use them to your advantage for getting through this cave?
Not a Rip-off of an existing series called "The 8 Worlds" I swear. This is desert plains, with a TON of coins to collect.
A battleship that Bowser has never used, even though it is still inhabited? Last level I ever save to Smaghetti. Goodbye and good luck beating this.
